<div class="iframeItem">
<p><a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2019-sep-dec.html#4_December_2019_(Imprisoned_terrorists)" target="_top"><b>Imprisoned terrorists</b></a><br>
<i>4 December 2019</i></p>
<p>
What to do with imprisoned Islamist terrorists <a target="_top" href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/nov/30/terrorists-prison-releases-mistakes-deaths">poses a conundrum,
world-wide</a>.
<p>
In Western countries the danger of Islamist terrorism is pretty small,
overall. The danger of being murdered by an Islamist terrorist is
tiny compared with the danger of being murdered for some other reason,
and unless you are black that too is small.
<p>
Thus, if we resist the pressure to freak out about this tiny danger, we
will find that releasing Islamist convicts at the end of their
sentences is an acceptably small risk in an otherwise-risky world.
<p>
Corbyn <a target="_top" href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/dec/01/jeremy-corbyn-calls-for-focus-on-rehabilitation-of-terrorists-in-prison">is resisting that pressure</a>.
</div>

