and reduced the collections of the rest. <a target="_top" href="http://citizensdefendinglibraries.blogspot.com/2019/03/defending-libraries-testimony-to-city.html">Now New York City is doing more
of the same</a>.
<p>
My favorite library branch, the Donnell Library Center, is where I
went to look for textbooks on many subjects. It was shut down in 2008
to sell the land to a hotel, and replaced 8 years later with a much
smaller library.
</div>

